       <div class="entry-content">
        <p>
         <span class="pibfi_pinterest ">
          <img alt="Sweet-Swedish-Wedding-in-the-Countryside-Stina-Kase-Photography (15 of 33)" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-557338" height="900" src="http://junebugweddings.com/wedding-blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/Sweet-Swedish-Wedding-in-the-Countryside-Stina-Kase-Photography-15-of-33-600x900.jpg" width="600"/>
          <span class="xc_pin" onclick="pin_this(event, 'http://pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=http://junebugweddings.com/wedding-blog/sweet-swedish-wedding-countryside/&amp;media=http://junebugweddings.com/wedding-blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/Sweet-Swedish-Wedding-in-the-Countryside-Stina-Kase-Photography-15-of-33-600x900.jpg&amp;description=Sweet Swedish Wedding in the Countryside')">
          </span>
         </span>
        </p>
        <p>
         From a handful of giant pink balloons to a
         <a href="http://www.jlmcouture.com/hayley-paige" onclick="_gaq.push(['_trackEvent', 'outbound-article', 'http://www.jlmcouture.com/hayley-paige', 'Hayley Paige']);" target="_blank">
          Hayley Paige
         </a>
         ballgown, every inch of Lazian and Samans wedding is a delight to see. The Swedish wedding in the countryside took place at a private mansion by the lake, making for a quiet and romantic getaway for the newlyweds and their guests.
         <a href="http://www.stinakase.com/" onclick="_gaq.push(['_trackEvent', 'outbound-article', 'http://www.stinakase.com/', 'Stina Kase Photography']);" target="_blank">
          Stina Kase Photography
         </a>
         captured the dreamiest portraits of the couple as the sun set over the lake in a swirl of pink that perfectly matched the pretty wedding dcor.
        </p>
        <p>
         <span style="font-size: 18pt;">
          <em>
           The Couple:
          </em>
         </span>
        </p>
        <p>
         Lazian and Saman
        </p>
        <p>
         <span style="font-size: 18pt;">
          <em>
           The Wedding:
          </em>
         </span>
        </p>
        <p>
         Private Residence, Sweden
        </p>
        <p>
         <span style="font-size: 18pt;">
          <em>
           The Inspiration:
          </em>
         </span>
        </p>
        <p>
         <em>
          It was a warm day in Stockholm and we had gathered friends and family in the beautiful garden. We said our vows under the two trees infront of the water surrounded by our closest family and friends. The day was filled with laughter and love. We chose soft natural colors that would melt in with the overall environment, soft pink, champagne and gold. The decor was fun and simple and we had the reception in a old stable house.
         </em>
        </p>

       <div class="entry-content">
        <p>
         <span class="pibfi_pinterest ">
          <img alt="Italian-Garden-Wedding-Inspiration-Rebecca-Silenzi (25 of 31)" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-557314" height="900" src="http://junebugweddings.com/wedding-blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/Italian-Garden-Wedding-Inspiration-Rebecca-Silenzi-25-of-31-600x900.jpg" width="600"/>
          <span class="xc_pin" onclick="pin_this(event, 'http://pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=http://junebugweddings.com/wedding-blog/italian-garden-wedding-inspiration/&amp;media=http://junebugweddings.com/wedding-blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/Italian-Garden-Wedding-Inspiration-Rebecca-Silenzi-25-of-31-600x900.jpg&amp;description=Italian Garden Wedding Inspiration')">
          </span>
         </span>
        </p>
        <p>
         <a href="http://www.bichiborghesi.it/" onclick="_gaq.push(['_trackEvent', 'outbound-article', 'http://www.bichiborghesi.it/', 'Villa Bichi Borghesi']);" target="_blank">
          Villa Bichi Borghesi
         </a>
         in Tuscany set the scene for this Italian garden styled photo shoot. From overgrown wisteria to garden-picked bouquets, every detail of the shoot portrays the incredible beauty of Italy. Two brides are shown wearing simple silk dresses thatare perfect for the light and airy feel of the garden setting.
        </p>
        <p>
         Heres what photographer
         <a href="http://www.rebeccasilenzi.com/" onclick="_gaq.push(['_trackEvent', 'outbound-article', 'http://www.rebeccasilenzi.com/', 'Rebecca Silenzi']);" target="_blank">
          Rebecca Silenzi
         </a>
         had to say about the inspiration behind the shoot:
        </p>
        <p>
         <em>
          The beautiful Italian garden is a perfect and idyllic spot for hosting an outdoor wedding reception in Tuscany during the spring surrounded by olive trees, majestic magnolias, roses and irises in the background. A few corners of the Villa that we have chosen as the backdrop for the style shoot are completely covered with wisteria. Our lovely bridal bouquet has been made using all the flowers we found in the garden  wild flowers, rosemary, artichokes, red salad, green hortensias all chosen to bring out the shades of marsala, carta da zucchero and green sage tones.
         </em>
        </p>
        <p>
         <em>
          Natalia Sorokina-Music did the table settings using crystal glasses, silver carved cutlery, marsala and carta da zucchero decorative lace elements which goes so well with the bridal bouquet, adorned with rosemary, wild flowers, grapes and olive branches. We used the rustic table and a couple of antic garden side tables as a setting for the cake and the guests.
         </em>
        </p>

       <div class="entry-content">
        <p>
         <span class="pibfi_pinterest ">
          <img alt="rachael schirano photography - jacquline patrick 0093" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-557281" height="900" src="http://junebugweddings.com/wedding-blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/rachael-schirano-photography-jacquline-patrick-0093-600x900.jpg" width="600"/>
          <span class="xc_pin" onclick="pin_this(event, 'http://pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=http://junebugweddings.com/wedding-blog/gorgeous-bloomington-normal-marriott-hotel-wedding/&amp;media=http://junebugweddings.com/wedding-blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/rachael-schirano-photography-jacquline-patrick-0093-600x900.jpg&amp;description=Gorgeous Bloomington-Normal Marriott Hotel Wedding')">
          </span>
         </span>
        </p>
        <p>
         On a cool fall day in Illinois, Jacqueline and Patrick tied the knot among changing leaves and their friends and family. The pastel color palette created a soft and romantic look for the day, just as Jacqueline had envisioned. The family-centered wedding included so many sweet moments between the couple and their loved ones, from the bride sharing a warm smile with her father before they walked down the aisle to the 14-person head table that seated each member of the bride and grooms family.
        </p>
        <p>
         <span style="font-size: 18pt;">
          <em>
           The Couple:
          </em>
         </span>
        </p>
        <p>
         Jacqueline and Patrick
        </p>
        <p>
         <span style="font-size: 18pt;">
          <em>
           The Wedding:
          </em>
         </span>
        </p>
        <p>
         <a href="http://www.marriott.com/hotels/travel/bmimc-bloomington-normal-marriott-hotel-and-conference-center/" onclick="_gaq.push(['_trackEvent', 'outbound-article', 'http://www.marriott.com/hotels/travel/bmimc-bloomington-normal-marriott-hotel-and-conference-center/', 'Bloomington-Normal Marriott Hotel']);" target="_blank">
          Bloomington-Normal Marriott Hotel
         </a>
         , Normal, Illinois
        </p>
        <p>
         <span style="font-size: 18pt;">
          <em>
           The Inspiration:
          </em>
         </span>
        </p>
        <p>
         <em>
          After the reality set in that we were going to get married, we quickly decided that we wanted to get married in our hometown the following fall, such a cozy time of year. All I could vision was a romantic day  filled with the natural fall beauty, delicate flowers, candlelight, and colors like soft whites, ivories, golds, peaches, pinks, and blues.
         </em>
        </p>

        <p>
         <span style="font-size: 18pt;">
          <em>
           The Moments:
          </em>
         </span>
        </p>
        <p>
         <em>
          Instead of a head table filled with our bridal party, we chose to have a family table that seated both of our families (all 14 of us!). I will never forget sitting at that table  all of us together and so happy. I couldnt stop thinking about how grateful I was, and will always be, for our families. We couldnt have been any happier. We were together and surrounded by the people we love the most.
         </em>
        </p>
        <p>
         <em>
          Another very special and favorite moment from our wedding day was my Dad and I doing our father/daughter choreographed dance to My Girl by the Temptations. We were both so nervous, and we even it practiced it in the church basement before walking down the aisle! It is a memory that we will never forget.
         </em>
        </p>
        <p>
         <span style="font-size: 18pt;">
          <em>
           The Couple Recommends:
          </em>
         </span>
        </p>
        <p>
         <em>
          Rachael Schirano and her amazing talent! She captured our day so candidly and so perfectly. She is so easy to work with and is passionate about what she does. I would recommend her to anyone looking for a photographer to capture something special.
         </em>
